http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/India-Art-Fair-begins/article14025353.ece

The eighth edition of the four-day India Art Fair began in the city on Thursday.About 70 galleries from across the world, with 18 of them participating for the first time, will take part in the annual fair. A number of international and national museums and foundations are presenting programmes or collaborations especially commissioned for the fair. The participants include the Delfina Foundation, Bhau Daji Lad Museum, Kiran Nadar Museum of Art, Jindal Art Centre and the Korean Cultural Centre of India. Entry tickets are priced at Rs.499, with discounts for students. The fair is on till January 31 at the NSIC Grounds in Okhla.